SECOND LEVEL PLAN
GROUND LEVEL PLAN
SAN
FRANCISCO
INTERNATIONAL
AIRPORT
NORTH TERMINAL
The major addition to the terminal ring is the North Terminal.
This three story structure will be 1050 feet long and contain
-350,000 sq. ft., plus a 140,000 sq. ft. basement in which
mechanical rooms, storage and baggage input are located.
The terminal serves 9 frontal aircraft gates and three new
rotundas accommodating 18 additional aircraft gates.
The second level provides baggage check-in and ticket
counter space for four major girlines, a large cocktail lounge
and food service facility, newsstand, gift shop, bank and
other concessions.
Two bridges and two tunnels connect the terminal to the
parking structure. The open planning of the terminal allows
through circulation to the frontal holding rooms and to the
connectors leading to the rotundas,
The ground level provides baggage return for arriving passengers
at 14 claim devices, plus airline and concession support facilities.
Passengers arriving from the rotunda and frontal gates descend to
the ground level by escalators and are directed to the claim device
for their flight by electronic signs. The passenger then proceeds
to the lower road curb or to the garage by tunnels.
The exterior finish will be precast concrete panels with exposed
grey granite aggregate. The grey glass will be set in black
aluminum frames.
